# Mobile Patient Table Columns

When building or modifying **patient tables** in professional dashboards (doctor, lab, nurse, clinic—old, new, future), use this pattern for "Last visit" / "Last request" columns so they display correctly on mobile.

## Pattern

**On mobile (< md):** Show only date and time (compact, no overflow).

**On desktop (md+):** Show full details (date, time, type, notes, fee, doctor name, status, etc.).

## Implementation

```tsx
<td className="p-4">
  <div className="text-sm">
    {lastVisitOrRequest ? (
      <>
        <p className="font-medium md:hidden">
          {new Date(date).toLocaleDateString()} {time && String(time).slice(0, 5)}
        </p>
        <div className="hidden md:block">
          <p className="font-medium">
            {new Date(date).toLocaleDateString()} {time && String(time).slice(0, 5)}
          </p>
          {/* Full details: type, notes, fee, doctor, status, etc. */}
        </div>
      </>
    ) : (
      <span className="text-muted-foreground">—</span>
    )}
  </div>
</td>
```

## Files to Keep in Sync

- `app/professional/dashboard/components/doctor-pro-dashboard.tsx` — Last visit
- `app/professional/dashboard/components/laboratory-pro-dashboard.tsx` — Last request
- Any new professional dashboard with patient tables

## Do NOT

- Show full details on mobile (causes overflow, cramped layout)
- Use `truncate` or `max-w` as the only mobile fix—use responsive visibility instead
